name: transmission network construction, electricity, medium voltage | transmission network, electricity, medium voltage | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/7772/documentation

This dataset describes the infrastructure (poles, cables etc.) of the electricity transmission network. It includes the high-to-medium voltage switching stations (above 2.5MVA).;Medium voltage level is considered to range between 1 kV and 24 kV Typically, medium to small scale industry, the service sector and public buildings are supplied from this voltage level (Itten et al. 2014). Smaller power plants feed their electricity production into this voltage level.;Reference(s): René Itten, Rolf Frischknecht, Matthias Stucki, 2014, Life Cycle Inventories of Electricity Mixes and Grid

The activity includes the land and material requirements of an average km of medium voltage transmission grid infrastructrure in Switzerland.

The activity ends with the disposal of the waste materials.It is assumed that 80 % of the cables are recycled.
category: F:Construction/42:Civil engineering/422:Construction of utility projects/4220:Construction of utility projects

processDocumentation.timeDescription: This dataset is based on a study by Itten et. al (2014), which is based on a number of literature sources representing the years 2010 and 2011. Due to the long lifetime, as well as project planning and construction times of ectricity transmission and distribution infrastructure, the 2010 situation is considered valid at least until 2020.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Average of medium voltage underground cables (29'629km) and aerial lines (13'042km) in Switzerland in 2010 (Itten et al. 2010). Switching stations use SF6.;The lifetime of the network is assumed to be 30 years (lifetime of most individual components assumed 40 years).

exchanges.description:
Wooden masts used for the medium voltage aireal lines are preserved by an inorganic preservative to prevent fouling. In Switzerland several preservative substances are forbidden; excludgin these, inorganic salt, containing Cr was assumed as the used type of preservative. The amount of preservatives used is based on literature sources (Werner et al. 2003; Künninger et al. 1995). Chromium vI, Copper Boron and Fluorine are wased out of the preserved masts into the soil with leachate rates of 60%, 75%, 95% and 80% respectively (Itten et al. 2014).
Reference(s): René Itten, Rolf Frischknecht, Matthias Stucki, 2014, Life Cycle Inventories of Electricity Mixes and Grid

exchanges.description:
Literature data; Federal office of the environment (FOEN) 2009, Swiss greenhouse gas statistics.
1% of total SF6 used in electricity transformation facilities is estimated to be emitted during construction, 1% during deconstruction, adding to 2% SF6 emitted of the total SF6 in use. 90% of SF6 in use is attributed to the high to medium votlage switch gear (considered in medium voltage network construction), 10% to the medium to low voltage switch gear (considered in low voltage network construction).
